race.comment: FORBIDDEN RIFF (7) has raced just twice since early August but is on a quicker back-up this time which is a good sign. Had a seven-week break before closing strongly to finish fourth over 1400m here last start. Fitter and the slightly longer trip is a plus. SPENZALOT (9) returned in good order last time out, making late inroads to grab third over 1300m at Scone. Has won up to 1400m and with that gallop under the belt should run another big race. CASH ME (1) has been freshened up since failing in an 1800m Midway at Randwick five weeks ago. Races well here including a win at the trip. Can return to form in this suitable contest. SCORCHED LANE (4) led and just failed to hold out today's rival TONG HO over 1400m here recently. Will give a great sight up front again. CAPE BYRON (3) disappointed in town last start after a comfortable win over 1400m here two back. In the right race to return to form.
